Title: Object: Admiral Walker
Series: Sir David Wilkie's Sketches in Turkey, Syria & Egypt, 1840 & 1841
Description: Portrait, three-quarters length standing to left, looking away to right, left hand tucked into his waist band, holding a curved sword in his left hand, resting against the crook of his arm. Hand-coloured lithograph printed in grey and beige
Curator's comments: From a set of lithographs 'Drawn on Stone by Joseph Nash', published in two volumes, London, 1843 and 1846 (1918,0205.2-8). See ODNB for Nash
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (379.5)
Associated names: Representation of: Sir Baldwin Wake Walker
